news.headline: JPMorgan Chase Ups Dividend, Approves $50 Billion Buyback After Stress Test
news.summary: The dividend increase and buyback come after the New York bank completed its stress test, which is used to assess an institution’s ability to withstand financial shocks and volatility.

news.headline: JPMorgan Chase stock rises after $50 billion buyback, dividend hike
news.summary: Investing.com -- JPMorgan Chase (NYSE:JPM) stock rose 1% in afterhours trading Tuesday following the banking giant’s announcement of a massive $50 billion share repurchase program and plans to increase its quarterly dividend.
